text:
AOE insider: "John Dee, John Wilkins, Christopher Wren, Robert Hooke, Robert Boyle, the Invisible College and the Royal Society in general ... all our guys."
"So you're saying the whole of Stephenson's Baroque Cycle is some kind of AOE celebration?"
"Ummm, duh!"
... I mean, Newton was obvious, but still.
... Maniac insists Euclid already knew the secret gang signs.
Steve's next "It's all about Black hairdressing" post is going to be lit.
Reads Blood Meridian once: "Scalping is a relatively functional military-commercial intersection point, actually."
... Scalping versus collecting ears controversy still ongoing.
Life is simply more fun when you've got Achilles on your team.
Steve has already won the 2024 Absolute Anglo Award.
Humans have done such a great job at ruling themselves that their legal code is metastatic cancer and AI threatens to understand that.
Totally. Been wondering about the best Anglo comeback to Nietzsche's smart-daft comments on Darwin, and Steve nails it perfectly.
It gets so lonely in the 'Hamas and the Epstein Network  both suck' quadrant.
